<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Combination Folder" class="currentChild" href="Combination_Folder">Combination Folder</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, a folding device which consists of folding units of both the <a title="Knife Folder" href="Knife_Folder">knife folder</a> and <a title="Buckle Folder" href="Buckle_Folder">buckle folder</a> design. Also known as a <a title="Combi" href="Combi">combi</a>. See <a title="Folding" href="Folding">Folding</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In <a title="Web Offset Lithography" href="Web_Offset_Lithography">web offset lithography</a>, a <em>combination folder</em> is an <a title="In-Line" href="In-Line">in-line</a> folding device which combines the <a title="former folder" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/former_folder">former folder</a>, <a title="Jaw Folder" href="Jaw_Folder">jaw folder</a>, and <a title="Chopper Folder" href="Chopper_Folder">chopper folder</a> configurations. 
</p>
